&gt; -----Original Message-----
&gt; From: tobemligado &lt;jasbell@...&gt;
&gt;
&gt; I have a singleton called &quot;ConfigManager&quot;, where in its constructor
&gt; it reads in a bunch of files from a directory and creates objectsfrom
&gt; the files.  I am doing this because I want to say &quot;ConfigManager is
&gt; not valid until these other objects have also been successfully
&gt; created&quot;.
&gt;
&gt; I want the &quot;ConfigManager&quot; to be able to read a directory full
&gt; of &quot;bad files&quot; in some test scenarios, a directory full of &quot;good
&gt; files&quot; in other test scenarios, and a directory full of &quot;good and bad
&gt; files&quot; in yet other test scenarios.  Ultimately, the program will
&gt; have to handle &quot;good and bad files&quot;,
&gt;
&gt; My problem is that I need to &quot;trick&quot; the &quot;ConfigManager&quot; into using
&gt; the three directories in different test scenarios, but I dont want to
&gt; alter the fact that all objects are created in &quot;ConfigManager&#39;s&quot;
&gt; constructor.  Here is what is in the constructor for the
&gt; singleton &quot;ConfigManager&quot;:
&gt; ----------------------------------------------------
&gt; String basePath = ServiceResources.CONFIG_FILE_DIRECTORY;
&gt; setBaseDirectory(basePath);
&gt; loadAllFilesFound(getBaseDirectory());
&gt; loadConfigFilesFound(getAllFilesFoundList());
&gt; ArrayList configList = createConfigurations(getConfigFilesFound());
&gt; TriggerManager tm = TriggerManager.getInstance();
&gt; ArrayList triggerList = tm.createTriggers(configList);
&gt; tm.registerTriggers(triggerList);
&gt; ----------------------------------------------------
&gt;
&gt; How can I switch the CONFIG_FILE_DIRECTORY value for testing when its
&gt; in the constructor?

Why can&#39;t you just change the value of
ServiceResources.CONFIG_FILE_DIRECTORY before you call ConfigManager&#39;s
constructor?

